examples.en: In this painting, the predominant colour is black.
Religion is the predominant theme of the play.
Italian opera became predominant at the end of the 17th century.
Islam is predominant in northern Africa, the Middle East, Pakistan, and Indonesia.
She is predominant among new writers.
The voices of dissentients were drowned by the predominant shout.
The predominant mood among policy-makers is optimism.
